cards.description:
An informative word used for resource information retrieval that indicates the content of a resource.

Relates to resources via P2.
cards.instructions: Select keywords associated with the resource.
cards.name: Keyword

cards.description:
Start/End dates for resources.  Assumed to be typed and within calendar time. 

Connects to Activity (E7) and Historical Event (E5) resource models via P114
Connects to Heritage Resource (E18) and Heritage Resource Group (E27) resource models via P12i
Connects to Actor (E39) resource model via P11i
cards.instructions: Record the start and end dates of the resource's existence.
cards.name: Start and End Dates

cards.description:
Describes the physical location of a heritage resource or heritage resource group.  Includes extra nodes for cadastral information.

Relates to Heritage Resource E18 with P53
Relates to Heritage Resource Group E27 with P89
cards.name: Place

cards.description: Represents a single node in a graph
cards.instructions: Describe the location of the resource.
cards.name: Description Location

cards.description:
Describes the modification of a Heritage Resource.

Connects to Heritage Resource (E18) via P12i
cards.instructions: Describe modification or alteration to the resource.
cards.name: Alterations

cards.description: Used to hold identifiers necessary to link a given resource to records in an external (perhaps legacy) system.
cards.instructions: Enter information for identifiers of the resource from other external sources.
cards.name: External Identifier

cards.instructions: This card ties together a Resource Type and Use Type with timeframe based on cultural period or actual dates.  For a separate combination Style and Use Type, create a separate entry.
cards.name: Archaeological Resource Type

cards.instructions: Define the spatial location.
cards.name: Spatial Location

cards.description:
Describes the type of resource. 

Applies to: Heritage Group, Heritage
cards.name: Resource Type Classification

cards.description: Physical thing on a heritage resource. Connect to Heritage Resource E18 via P46
cards.instructions: Select the architectural component and the component's material and technique
cards.name: Component

cards.description: Represents a single node in a graph
cards.instructions: For Historic Resources only, define the setting of the historic resource.
cards.name: Setting Type

cards.instructions: This card ties together a Style and Use Type with timeframe based on cultural period or actual dates.  For a separate combination Style and Use Type, create a separate entry.
cards.name: Style

cards.instructions: This card ties together a Related/Acillary Features and Use Type with timeframe based on cultural period or actual dates.  For a separate combination Related/Ancillary Features and Use Type, create a separate entry.
cards.name: Related/Ancillary Feature

cards.description:
Captures information about special status, protection, or privileges afforded under law.

Applies to: Heritage Resource, Heritage Resource Model
cards.name: Right

cards.description:
The Measurement branch measures instances of a Heritage Resource E18 or a Heritage Resource Group E27

Relates to those resource models via P39i
cards.instructions: Capture the measurements associated to this resource.
cards.name: Measurement

cards.description:
Generic branch for capturing free-form written descriptive information.
Intended to be evolution from v3 description branch from HIP 3. Created semantic description node with description string and description type hanging off of it. Description (semantic node) becomes a grouping node (type and string).  

This branch meets technical business rules for CRM compliance but CRM experts have said that this is an inappropriate implementation of E62.

Connects to all resources with P140i
cards.instructions: Enter a description and description type for the resource.
cards.name: Description

cards.description: Represents a single node in a graph
cards.instructions: Select the administrative/governmental subdivision name and type.
cards.name: Administration Subdivision

cards.description: Represents a single node in a graph
cards.instructions: Enter the cadastral reference number.
cards.name: Cadastral Reference

cards.description:
The name of a resource.

Applies to Heritage Resource, Heritage Resource Group, Activity, and Historical Event.  Actors receive their "names" from the Appellation branch.
cards.instructions: Enter a name for the resource and name type (i.e.  Primary, Alternative, etc.)  You may add additional names as necessary.
cards.name: Name

cards.description: Describes the conditions, threats, and disturbances affecting a Heritage Resource or Heritage Resource Group. Additional information may include a management recommendation, a condition image, the data the condition was assessed and a description of the condition.
cards.instructions: One assessment of condition at a particular point in time.
cards.name: Condition Assessment

cards.description:
Phase Type Assignments for Heritage Resource E18.

Connects via P92i
cards.name: Archaeological Resource Type

cards.description: This branch consists of a reference image or thumbnail.
cards.instructions: Upload a reference image(s) for the resource.
cards.name: Reference Image
